Description

The Database class represents the storage for various entities in the system.

The Day enum represents days of the week.

The Dean class represents a dean user in the system.
Emergency
The Emergency enum represents different levels of emergency.
Employee
The Employee class represents an employee user in the system.

The EmployeeFactory class is responsible for creating different types of employees based on the user's choice.

LanguageInterface
 
Lesson
The Lesson class represents a lesson in an system.

The `LessonTime` class represents the time for a lesson, including the day of the week, start time, and end time.
Log
The Log class represents a log entry in the system.
Manager
The Manager class represents a manager in the academic system.
Mark
The Mark class represents the mark of course for a student, including two attestations and a final exam.
News
The News class represents a news article with a topic, title, text, and associated comments.
Observed
The Observed interface represents an observable entity that can be observed by users.
Order
The Order class represents a support order created by a employee.
Organisation
The Organisation class represents an organization with a name, a head (student), and members.
PaperCitationsComparator
The PaperCitationsComparator class is a comparator for sorting research papers based on the number of citations.
PaperDateComparator
The PaperDateComparator class is a comparator for sorting research papers based on the date of papers.
PaperPagesComparator
The `PaperPagesComparator` class is a comparator for sorting research papers based on the number of pages.
Request
The Request class represents a request (it also can be complaint) made by an employee to the dean.
Researcher<T>
The Researcher class represents a researcher in the academic system.
ResearcherCitationsComparator
The ResearcherCitationsComparator class is a comparator for comparing researchers based on the total number of citations received for their research papers.
ResearchJournal
The ResearchJournal class represents a research journal that contains research papers and notifies its subscribers about new publications.
ResearchPaper
The ResearchPaper class represents a research paper with citations, name, number of pages, doi.
ResearchProject
The ResearchProject class represents a research project that consists of multiple research papers.
RussianLanguage
 
SortStudents
The SortStudents class is a comparator for sorting students based on their GPA in ascending order.
StaticMethods
The StaticMethods class contains static utility methods used throughout the application.
Status
The Status enum represents different statuses in a system for orders and requests.
Student
The Student class represents a student in the academic system.
StudentFactory
The StudentFactory class is responsible for creating instances of the Student class and its subclasses, such as GraduateStudent.
Teacher
The Teacher class represents a teacher in the system.
TeacherTitle
The TeacherTitle enum represents different titles for teachers.
TechSupportSpecialist
The TechSupportSpecialist class represents a technical support specialist who can view, accept, and reject orders.

The TypeLesson enum represents different types of lessons.
TypeManager
The TypeManager enum represents different types of managers in a system.
User
The User class is an abstract class representing a generic user in the system.
